FBIS3-47963 "dreas014_a_94034" FBIS-EAS-94-014 Document Type:Daily Report 21 January 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Hosokawa Calls Stable Employment `Top Priority' OW2101040094 Tokyo KYODO in English 1242 GMT 20 Jan 94 OW2101040094 Tokyo KYODO Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Tokyo, Jan. 21 KYODO -- Prime Minister Morihiro Hosokawa said Friday [21 January] that ensuring a stable employment environment is one of the top priority jobs for the government. Hosokawa told the second meeting of a special cabinet forum on employment that the government needs to put into practice as early as possible a program of creating more jobs that was worked out in mid-December by the Labor Ministry. Finance Minister Hirohisa Fujii, also present at the meeting, pledged fiscal support for the program, while Minister of International Trade and Industry Hiroshi Kumagai said his ministry plans to nurture promising industries such as biotechnology, new energy and information to create new jobs. Labor Minister Chikara Sakaguchi, meanwhile, called for an early drafting of a new economic pump-primer by the government, saying improvement in the labor climate needs recovery of the economy.
